Introduction
Welcome to the HR System ESS app, developed by [Your Company Name]. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your personal information is handled in a safe and responsible manner. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application.

Information We Collect
Personal Information:

When you use our app, we may collect personal information such as your name, employee ID, contact details, and other information related to your employment.
Location Data:

Our app collects your geographic location data to provide location-based attendance tracking. This data is used to record your clock-in and clock-out times based on your physical location.
Device Information:

We may collect information about your device, including its model, operating system, unique device identifiers, and mobile network information.
App Usage Information:

We collect information about your interaction with our app, such as the features you use and the actions you take.
Use of QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES Permission
The HR System ESS app uses the QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES permission to enhance the functionality of our location-based attendance tracking feature. Specifically, this permission allows us to:

Verify Location Service Dependencies: Ensure that the necessary system services for location tracking are active and functioning on your device.
Enhance Security: Confirm that your device is securely configured and complies with our company’s policies regarding location tracking.
Optimize Performance: Select and use the most appropriate services available on your device for accurate and efficient location updates.
We do not use this permission to access or collect data from other apps on your device beyond what is necessary to ensure the proper functioning of our location services.

How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:

Provide, operate, and maintain the HR System ESS app.
Track and manage your attendance based on your location.
Improve our app’s functionality and user experience.
Communicate with you about your employment and related services.
Ensure compliance with legal and regulatory requirements.
How We Share Your Information
We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information with:

Authorized Personnel: Access to your information is limited to authorized personnel who need it to perform their job functions.
Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers who assist us in operating our app, such as cloud storage services.
Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required by law or in response to legal processes.
Data Security
We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information. Your data is stored securely and is only accessible to authorized personnel. However, please be aware that no security measures are perfect, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.

Your Choices
You have the right to:

Access and update your personal information.
Withdraw your consent for us to collect and process your data.
Request deletion of your data, subject to legal and contractual obligations.
Children’s Privacy
Our app is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected personal information from a child under 18, we will take steps to delete that information.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the updated Privacy Policy will take effect immediately upon posting.

